Notebook[{
Cell["Visualization", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"dbb8c5f3-3aec-434b-b8a5-ad583550aad3"],

Cell["\<\
The visualization layer organises everything the paclet knows about drawing \
geometric objects on graphs. It has three pieces: the diffuse-rendering \
primitive InfraSceneHighlight, the declarative scene language built around \
InfraScene, and a family of Manipulate-based viewers for interactive \
exploration. All paths converge on the same head dispatch (Points / Paths / \
Cycles / Sets) and the same opacity/thickness/point-size envelope, so the \
visual language is consistent whether you call a viewer, render a Find* \
result directly, or evaluate a multi-step InfraScene.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cff84da4-8666-4faf-ad51-2c35995e1a07"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"95c29583-ad3c-4fc1-8a95-9e2558602f50"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"5819a578-1dac-4264-b553-6c0bdaf47c96"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"d0c939dc-7891-4a4b-8e32-8a94b5c79b7e"],

Cell["Diffuse-rendering primitive", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"cae3fd7a-9913-419c-8124-481a5615d52d"],

Cell["\<\
A multi-object is a list of representations of the same geometric object. \
InfraSceneHighlight takes a list of multi-objects (each optionally with a \
colour) and emits a HighlightGraph with opacity / thickness / point-size \
scaled to within-object multiplicity.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d11aa327-c837-42cc-8841-d0b10d7ba6c6"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight -- the sole rendering primitive; every viewer and every \
notebook calls into this.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0dbd6226-dc9d-4ef2-bcd0-ec521a7148ea"],

Cell["\<\
Multi-object wrappers (the heads InfraSceneHighlight dispatches on)\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b78ea301-bb40-46db-9d0c-f5107b80d171"],

Cell["\<\
Each Find* function returns a wrapped multi-realisation object. The \
single-_List-arg form is the rendering signature; the wrappers also serve as \
scene-language constructors with different arities.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7adf0b40-3b60-44f3-9ec9-d61aff825c84"],

Cell["InfraPoint -- vertices, no edges (Points dispatch).", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"de8ee44b-0479-4ff7-8571-082a4bf4203e"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSegment -- sequential edges via Partition (Paths dispatch).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f95bf34a-4a12-4032-bfff-62998ece74ec"],

Cell["\<\
InfraLine -- sequential edges, used by FindLine in scene-language form (Paths \
dispatch).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"fd17b2de-3c86-45f5-81fb-364b05d672b1"],

Cell["\<\
InfraShell -- induced subgraph of the level surface (Sets dispatch).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0acdffc8-3cb4-44b1-ab7f-46fc67fb7ec3"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPlane -- induced subgraph of the bisecting hyperplane (Sets dispatch).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b0c343fc-2fbd-4f72-9150-539e13dcaf16"],

Cell["\<\
InfraCircle -- sequential edges with auto-closure (Cycles dispatch).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9fc468b2-c014-4914-8acb-7ed619dd7af0"],

Cell["\<\
InfraRay -- sequential edges; rays at a base vertex O (Paths dispatch).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"701b62a7-5feb-4cb3-871a-bd4b6dba7cc6"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPencil -- multi-CONSTITUENT wrapper (entries are InfraRay objects, one \
per direction class); flattens through [\"Rays\"] before dispatching to Paths.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"29c67f71-42da-441b-8274-375509ac962e"],

Cell["\<\
Wrapper accessors apply uniformly: [\"Realizations\"] (bare list), \
[\"Length\"], [\"Expand\"], [\"First\"]; wrapper[[i]] returns a wrapped \
singleton, not the bare realisation.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1191534a-87cf-4529-bf97-24344bdc89ce"],

Cell["Declarative scene engine", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3b6d53f3-f922-40de-9730-979c8e02bb7b"],

Cell["\<\
InfraScene lets you describe a geometric configuration symbolically (objects \
+ hypotheses), compute every binding consistent with the hypotheses on a \
given graph, and read out the resulting branches.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7ba5b4fb-f799-4dc3-9c16-b4920a81d063"],

Cell["\<\
InfraScene -- scene descriptor: objects + hypotheses (constructions and \
assertions).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"40e4b367-cff9-416f-b0ef-a8cb12b5b969"],

Cell["\<\
FindInfraScene -- evaluates every step of the scene on a graph; returns a \
list of InfraInstance objects, one per branch. Accepts pre-fixed bindings.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d2f05e36-3e01-40c9-8522-c7c603fc9401"],

Cell["\<\
InfraInstance -- wraps a solved binding association; read out via \
InfraInstance[inst, sym] or InfraInstance[inst, {sym1, sym2, ...}].\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"79213570-cfe0-4657-a2c2-dad37c74edeb"],

Cell["\<\
InfraGeometricStep -- groups hypotheses into a manual construction step \
(overrides the auto-computed dependency level ordering).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"ec7248fd-3ee3-4bf1-a22e-9f4ab978a778"],

Cell["Scene constructions (multi-arg signatures of the same heads)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c5e98344-b884-447c-8191-f560fe973e83"],

Cell["\<\
Inside an InfraScene, the wrapper heads carry constructor signatures distinct \
from the single-_List-arg rendering signature. The two forms never collide.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2c51a3cb-4f94-4e4f-a7b0-36e2a850fb93"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPoint[v] / InfraPoint[origin, dist] / InfraPoint[\"Center\"] / \
InfraPoint[\"Periphery\"] / InfraPoint[n] -- specify a point.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2dc35255-d3d5-40f7-aa38-d557d80a2530"],

Cell["InfraSegment[p, q] -- a geodesic between p and q.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"98d8de0a-2de1-48b0-a70e-64c19c07d427"],

Cell["\<\
InfraLine[p, q] / InfraLine[path] -- a maximal-geodesic line.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d2794f0c-7503-4001-a1da-179c5dfe8510"],

Cell["InfraShell[c, r] -- the level surface { v : d(c, v) = r }.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"64a1ea43-e223-4910-9e54-3fa72f7a7ace"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPlane[p1, p2] / InfraPlane[p1, p2, {lo, hi}] -- the bisecting hyperplane \
between p1 and p2 (with optional distance-difference window).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f8f1b71c-d660-49f0-9c95-04a1da096af6"],

Cell["\<\
InfraCircle[c, r] -- a separating cycle in the level-surface subgraph.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"26cfb512-f490-49d9-8f90-ada8955e527c"],

Cell["Scene assertions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"200a7c29-8e2e-400d-a876-d635fddcea13"],

Cell["\<\
Assertion-flavoured heads test predicates inside a scene's hypothesis list. \
They resolve to the bare *Q predicates with the current bindings substituted.\
\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c9a31e62-32ce-4c36-a37d-255825361f1e"],

Cell["InfraSegmentQ -- s is a valid geodesic segment.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b9d65b10-b976-4f32-be72-1df1d90efa76"],

Cell["InfraLineQ -- s is a maximal geodesic.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"6fc84fd6-b35f-4f5c-9c87-a4e59965cc3c"],

Cell["InfraShellQ -- vs is a valid metric shell.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"03655dc9-ef1a-41c4-83b1-017e876d36a5"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPlaneQ -- h is a valid bisecting hyperplane between p1 and p2.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"590af5bd-b9d4-4087-bf3c-d0ca91f7c34b"],

Cell["\<\
InfraCircleQ -- c is a valid metric circle (separating cycle).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9c8a4a26-41fa-46a3-80b7-f565d2249e7a"],

Cell["InfraParallelQ -- two lines are parallel.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9ed6806c-dee2-4ee0-ba4f-39841a50c1d4"],

Cell["InfraIntersectQ -- two sets intersect.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"26c3e6f4-b041-4de6-a743-b53b74779c69"],

Cell["\<\
InfraIntersection / InfraDistance -- structural heads (intersection vertex \
set, graph distance).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"78f3a8d4-5969-4ac6-8229-5d6cee4c9192"],

Cell["Interactive viewers", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7e96a096-ad68-49b6-aa3d-4a62787f9d38"],

Cell["\<\
Manipulate-based shells over the Find* family. Each one is a thin wrapper: it \
calls the corresponding Find* with All, runs the chosen path-space selector, \
and feeds the result into InfraSceneHighlight.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d5fc0bdd-a2b1-4fcc-ac6e-398e875c0d51"],

Cell["PointViewer -- sliders for points, From source, separation.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"52da018f-fc1d-4133-b1bc-6cdadc9cf5c0"],

Cell["\<\
SegmentViewer -- two endpoints + path-space selector + count.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a47ef89d-1e47-4615-85de-c5ffdb4ecfbf"],

Cell["\<\
ShellViewer -- center + radius + Method (Metric / Separating).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"6f81faee-2374-4b6f-8052-cf566fb90447"],

Cell["CircleViewer -- center + radius + path-space selector.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"35043494-3b48-467b-9f29-075975c0a097"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneViewer -- step-by-step navigation of an InfraScene with branch / \
fix-and-advance / reset controls; aggregate vs single-instance modes.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5c44ad3f-122d-4003-98a5-4766f6919b8c"],

Cell["Diffuse-rendering envelope", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2c4b5dba-5ad9-43e3-a23e-52d4973e07b8"],

Cell["\<\
Within one multi-object, vertex / edge intensity scales with how many \
representations pass through. Across multi-objects, colours blend on shared \
vertices / edges. Default colour is by head -- InfraPoint, InfraSegment / \
InfraLine, InfraShell, InfraPlane, InfraCircle, InfraRay, InfraPencil each \
have a palette entry; unwrapped entries fall through to a cycling palette.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f23567a4-ab03-4ba9-9124-bea249f69f71"],

Cell["\<\
Tune via options OpacityRange, ThicknessRange, PointSizeRange on \
InfraSceneHighlight.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b9917036-de4e-4dae-92da-e8cf23416a06"],

Cell["\<\
Wrap as `entry -> color` to override the default palette assignment.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"cb8f8c4f-68b1-45e2-9853-955458957362"],

Cell["Tutorial", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"80f103d4-e3ad-48ec-b7a5-a650cdb2e150"],

Cell["\<\
See VisualizationTutorial for runnable examples on grids, paths, and small \
cycles.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"11a81c85-9e2c-4c64-bac1-b6900fab0ade"],

Cell["See also", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"08f2bab7-7b37-472d-a556-7f353af5a151"],

Cell["\<\
EuclideanGeometryGuide -- the Find* family that produces the multi-objects.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7d8979d1-dba9-497b-9ef3-8a4c6f1a78ae"],

Cell["\<\
ProjectiveGeometryGuide -- pencils and rays, rendered through the same \
diffuse-rendering primitive.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1c94faea-672e-4589-97bb-6d411cb4b469"],

Cell["TarskiGeometryGuide -- predicates that drive scene assertions.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"ce7a2d03-c5f0-4bf0-b71d-5aee68a66498"],

Cell["References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"40bb3003-f444-468d-a737-a11db1fa3e10"],

Cell["\<\
Wolfram, GeometricScene system reference, \
https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/GeometricScene.html (the closest \
design analogue for InfraScene).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"602499f6-0868-4fb5-a8f2-77ccc291ba80"]
},
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Mac OS X ARM (64-bit) (July 8, 2025)",
